umlElement.title: Library
umlElement.notes: The Library API allows both Librarians & Borrowers to interact with relevant data in the Library system.

umlElement.title: Adult Borrower
umlElement.notes: A Borrower who can borrow any media and can vouch for Junior Borrowers.

umlElement.title: Borrower
umlElement.notes: The abstract concept of a Borrower. Actual Borrowers must be either Adult or Junior.

umlElement.title: Junior Borrower
umlElement.notes: A Borrower who cannot borrow certain Media Titles and a limited number of Media Copies.

umlElement.title: Librarian
umlElement.notes: A Librarian who can order copies of MediaTitles and may act as a manager or mentor for other librarians.

umlElement.title: Loan
umlElement.notes: The Loan of a specific Media Copy

umlElement.title: Media Copy
umlElement.notes: An actual copy of a MediaTitle that can be borrowed.

umlElement.title: Media Title
umlElement.notes: Details of a Media Title, such as a Book or Movie. This is distinct from a Media Copy which is a particular

umlElement.title: Reservation
umlElement.notes: The Reservation of a Media Title, independent of which actual copy is subsequently loaned.

umlElement.title: Media Type
umlElement.notes: The types of MediaTitle that the library holds.

umlElement.title: top genres
umlElement.notes: For the specified number of towns, the number of loans for each Genre is returned.

umlElement.title: county stats
umlElement.notes: Gets the statistics for each County. For each Town and Borrower the total number of Loans is retrieved.

umlElement.title: dob
umlElement.notes: The Date of Birth (DOB) of this Junior Borrower

umlElement.title: BOOK
umlElement.notes: The BOOK Literal description.

umlElement.title: VIDEO
umlElement.notes: The VIDEO Literal description.

umlElement.title: AUDIO
umlElement.notes: The AUDIO Literal description.

umlElement.title: library
umlElement.notes: The Library model contains the key types and depends on the core-types and the personal details packages.

umlElement.title: Personal Details
umlElement.notes: Defines a model of the abstract concept of a Person, its properties and relationships. Various types specialize Person such as Adult Borrower & Librarian.

umlElement.title: Address
umlElement.notes: An Address that Borrowers currently or previously have lived at.

umlElement.title: Personal Details
umlElement.notes: The abstract Person type, which is specialized by the Borrower and Librarian types, and its associations

umlElement.title: Core Types
umlElement.notes: Updated to add Error type

umlElement.title: Primitives
umlElement.notes: Initial version of Primitive types library.

umlElement.title: Error
umlElement.notes: An RFC 7807 compliant type to report an error to the client.

umlElement.title: Boolean
umlElement.notes: A representation of objects that can have two values: true and false.

umlElement.title: Byte
umlElement.notes: A signed 8-bit integer, ranges from -128 to 127

umlElement.title: Char
umlElement.notes: An single character.

umlElement.title: Date
umlElement.notes: An ISO 8601 standard representation of a date.

umlElement.title: DateTime
umlElement.notes: An ISO 8601 standard representation of a date & time.

umlElement.title: Double
umlElement.notes: A 64-bit floating point number that adheres to the IEEE 754 double-precision standard .

umlElement.title: Fixed
umlElement.notes: Representation of fractional number using integer with defined specific number of bits reserved for the integer part and a specific number of bits reserved for the fractional part.

umlElement.title: Float
umlElement.notes: A 32-bit floating point number that adheres to the IEEE 754 single-precision standard .

umlElement.title: ID
umlElement.notes: A unique identifier within the scope of the relevant instance.

umlElement.title: Int
umlElement.notes: A signed 32-bit integer, ranges from --2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647

umlElement.title: Short
umlElement.notes: A signed 16-bit integer, ranges from -32768 to 32767

umlElement.title: String
umlElement.notes: A sequence of characters.

umlElement.title: UNDEFINED
umlElement.notes: Used by the Model Transform Tools (MTT) to show where no type has been defined within a UML model.

umlElement.title: URI
umlElement.notes: A representation of a Uniform Resource Identifier.

umlElement.title: UUID
umlElement.notes: A Universally Unique Identifier.

umlElement.title: Void
umlElement.notes: A void or null type. Often used as the return type for a function that does not return a defined type.
